.TH TREE-STYLE-TERMINAL 1 "24 July 2026" "Tree Style Terminal 0.8.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tree-style-terminal, tst \- manage terminal sessions in a tree
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tree-style-terminal
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ directory ]
.br
.B tst
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ directory ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Tree Style Terminal
is a GTK 3 terminal emulator that organizes VTE terminal sessions in a
hierarchical tree instead of a row of tabs.
.PP
.B tst
is an equivalent short command.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-dpi " " DPI
Override the detected display DPI.
.TP
.BR \-\-show-info
Print display and font diagnostics while starting the application.
.TP
.BR \-\-test-fonts
Print font scaling diagnostics and exit.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress the startup message.
.TP
.BR \-\-log-level " " LEVEL
Set diagnostic verbosity to
.BR debug ,
.BR info ,
.BR warning ,
.BR error ,
or
.BR critical .
.TP
.BR \-\-working-directory " " DIRECTORY
.TQ
.BR \-\-workdir " " DIRECTORY
Create the first terminal session in
.IR DIRECTORY .
.TP
.BR \-p " " FILE
.TQ
.BR \-\-profile " " FILE
Load a YAML workspace profile.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show the command-line help.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for the configuration file. The default is
.IR ~/.config .
.TP
.B SHELL
Shell started in new terminal sessions. The Debian fallback is
.IR /bin/bash .
.TP
.B TST_DPI
Alternative display DPI override.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ${XDG_CONFIG_HOME:-~/.config}/tree-style-terminal/config.yaml
User configuration. A commented template is created on first configuration
load.
.SH NOTES
This release does not implement Debian's
.B x-terminal-emulator
command-line contract and therefore is not registered as that alternative.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bash (1),
.BR update-alternatives (1)
.PP
Full configuration and workspace profile documentation is installed under
.IR /usr/share/doc/tree-style-terminal/ .
